2.1 Planning for traveller sites
The government’s planning policy for traveller sites requires local planning
authorities to assess the accommodation needs of Gypsy and Travellers in
their local area and, where there is a need for Traveller sites, identify land for
sites in their local plans. When plan making, local authorities should consider
how they can ensure that Gypsy and Traveller sites are sustainable
economically, socially and environmentally. The Commons Library briefing on
planning provisions for Gypsies and Travellers in England provides further
information.
